@startuml jad-deployment
' JAD stack deployment — sources: CLAUDE.md "Key Services" table (pre-restructure,
' now .claude/rules + docs/knowledge/services/), docker-compose.jad.yml,
' scripts/azure/env.sh (ACA app names).
title JAD stack — local Docker Compose / Azure Container Apps (rg-mvhd-dev)

node "UI tier" {
  [Next.js 14 UI\nport 3000 / mvhd-ui] as UI
}
node "Identity" {
  [Keycloak (realm edcv)\nport 8080 / mvhd-keycloak] as KC
  [Vault (in-memory!)\nport 8200 / mvhd-vault] as VAULT
  [IdentityHub / mvhd-identityhub] as IH
  [IssuerService / mvhd-issuerservice] as IS
}
node "Data tier" {
  database "Neo4j 5\n7687/7474 / mvhd-neo4j" as N4
  database "PostgreSQL\n5432 / mvhd-postgres" as PG
  [neo4j-proxy (Express)\nport 9090 / mvhd-neo4j-proxy] as PX
}
node "Dataspace" {
  [EDC controlplane / mvhd-controlplane] as CP
  [dataplane FHIR / mvhd-dp-fhir] as DPF
  [dataplane OMOP / mvhd-dp-omop] as DPO
}
node "Federation (issue #8)" {
  [catalog-crawler\nACA job */5min] as CRAWL
  [catalog-enricher / mvhd-catalog-enricher] as ENR
  queue "NATS 4222 / mvhd-nats" as NATS
}

UI --> KC : OIDC (confidential + PKCE S256)
UI --> PX : FHIR / OMOP / NLQ / federated
PX --> N4 : bolt
CP --> PG
IH --> PG
CRAWL --> N4 : crawl targets
CRAWL --> NATS : dataspace.catalog.raw
NATS --> ENR
ENR --> N4 : MERGE federated datasets
@enduml
